83 X86InstrInfo::X86InstrInfo(X86Subtarget &STI)
84  : X86GenInstrInfo((STI.isTarget64BitLP64() ? X86::ADJCALLSTACKDOWN64
85  : X86::ADJCALLSTACKDOWN32),
86  (STI.isTarget64BitLP64() ? X86::ADJCALLSTACKUP64
87  : X86::ADJCALLSTACKUP32),
88  X86::CATCHRET,
89  (STI.is64Bit() ? X86::RET64 : X86::RET32)),
90  Subtarget(STI), RI(STI.getTargetTriple()) {
91 }

93 bool
94 X86InstrInfo::isCoalescableExtInstr(const MachineInstr &MI,
95  Register &SrcReg, Register &DstReg,
96  unsigned &SubIdx) const {
97  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
98  default: break;
99  case X86::MOVSX16rr8:
100  case X86::MOVZX16rr8:
101  case X86::MOVSX32rr8:
102  case X86::MOVZX32rr8:
103  case X86::MOVSX64rr8:
104  if (!Subtarget.is64Bit())
105  // It's not always legal to reference the low 8-bit of the larger
106  // register in 32-bit mode.
107  return false;
108  [[fallthrough]];
109  case X86::MOVSX32rr16:
110  case X86::MOVZX32rr16:
111  case X86::MOVSX64rr16:
112  case X86::MOVSX64rr32: {
113  if (MI.getOperand(0).getSubReg() || MI.getOperand(1).getSubReg())
114  // Be conservative.
115  return false;
116  SrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
117  DstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
118  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
119  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
120  case X86::MOVSX16rr8:
121  case X86::MOVZX16rr8:
122  case X86::MOVSX32rr8:
123  case X86::MOVZX32rr8:
124  case X86::MOVSX64rr8:
125  SubIdx = X86::sub_8bit;
126  break;
127  case X86::MOVSX32rr16:
128  case X86::MOVZX32rr16:
129  case X86::MOVSX64rr16:
130  SubIdx = X86::sub_16bit;
131  break;
132  case X86::MOVSX64rr32:
133  SubIdx = X86::sub_32bit;
134  break;
135  }
136  return true;
137  }
138  }
139  return false;
140 }
141 
142 bool X86InstrInfo::isDataInvariant(MachineInstr &MI) {
143  if (MI.mayLoad() || MI.mayStore())
144  return false;
145 
146  // Some target-independent operations that trivially lower to data-invariant
147  // instructions.
148  if (MI.isCopyLike() || MI.isInsertSubreg())
149  return true;
150 
151  unsigned Opcode = MI.getOpcode();
152  using namespace X86;
153  // On x86 it is believed that imul is constant time w.r.t. the loaded data.
154  // However, they set flags and are perhaps the most surprisingly constant
155  // time operations so we call them out here separately.
156  if (isIMUL(Opcode))
157  return true;
158  // Bit scanning and counting instructions that are somewhat surprisingly
159  // constant time as they scan across bits and do other fairly complex
160  // operations like popcnt, but are believed to be constant time on x86.
161  // However, these set flags.
162  if (isBSF(Opcode) || isBSR(Opcode) || isLZCNT(Opcode) || isPOPCNT(Opcode) ||
163  isTZCNT(Opcode))
164  return true;
165  // Bit manipulation instructions are effectively combinations of basic
166  // arithmetic ops, and should still execute in constant time. These also
167  // set flags.
168  if (isBLCFILL(Opcode) || isBLCI(Opcode) || isBLCIC(Opcode) ||
169  isBLCMSK(Opcode) || isBLCS(Opcode) || isBLSFILL(Opcode) ||
170  isBLSI(Opcode) || isBLSIC(Opcode) || isBLSMSK(Opcode) || isBLSR(Opcode) ||
171  isTZMSK(Opcode))
172  return true;
173  // Bit extracting and clearing instructions should execute in constant time,
174  // and set flags.
175  if (isBEXTR(Opcode) || isBZHI(Opcode))
176  return true;
177  // Shift and rotate.
178  if (isROL(Opcode) || isROR(Opcode) || isSAR(Opcode) || isSHL(Opcode) ||
179  isSHR(Opcode) || isSHLD(Opcode) || isSHRD(Opcode))
180  return true;
181  // Basic arithmetic is constant time on the input but does set flags.
182  if (isADC(Opcode) || isADD(Opcode) || isAND(Opcode) || isOR(Opcode) ||
183  isSBB(Opcode) || isSUB(Opcode) || isXOR(Opcode))
184  return true;
185  // Arithmetic with just 32-bit and 64-bit variants and no immediates.
186  if (isADCX(Opcode) || isADOX(Opcode) || isANDN(Opcode))
187  return true;
188  // Unary arithmetic operations.
189  if (isDEC(Opcode) || isINC(Opcode) || isNEG(Opcode))
190  return true;
191  // Unlike other arithmetic, NOT doesn't set EFLAGS.
192  if (isNOT(Opcode))
193  return true;
194  // Various move instructions used to zero or sign extend things. Note that we
195  // intentionally don't support the _NOREX variants as we can't handle that
196  // register constraint anyways.
197  if (isMOVSX(Opcode) || isMOVZX(Opcode) || isMOVSXD(Opcode) || isMOV(Opcode))
198  return true;
199  // Arithmetic instructions that are both constant time and don't set flags.
200  if (isRORX(Opcode) || isSARX(Opcode) || isSHLX(Opcode) || isSHRX(Opcode))
201  return true;
202  // LEA doesn't actually access memory, and its arithmetic is constant time.
203  if (isLEA(Opcode))
204  return true;
205  // By default, assume that the instruction is not data invariant.
206  return false;
207 }

209 bool X86InstrInfo::isDataInvariantLoad(MachineInstr &MI) {
210  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
211  default:
212  // By default, assume that the load will immediately leak.
213  return false;
214 
215  // On x86 it is believed that imul is constant time w.r.t. the loaded data.
216  // However, they set flags and are perhaps the most surprisingly constant
217  // time operations so we call them out here separately.
218  case X86::IMUL16rm:
219  case X86::IMUL16rmi8:
220  case X86::IMUL16rmi:
221  case X86::IMUL32rm:
222  case X86::IMUL32rmi8:
223  case X86::IMUL32rmi:
224  case X86::IMUL64rm:
225  case X86::IMUL64rmi32:
226  case X86::IMUL64rmi8:
227 
228  // Bit scanning and counting instructions that are somewhat surprisingly
229  // constant time as they scan across bits and do other fairly complex
230  // operations like popcnt, but are believed to be constant time on x86.
231  // However, these set flags.
232  case X86::BSF16rm:
233  case X86::BSF32rm:
234  case X86::BSF64rm:
235  case X86::BSR16rm:
236  case X86::BSR32rm:
237  case X86::BSR64rm:
238  case X86::LZCNT16rm:
239  case X86::LZCNT32rm:
240  case X86::LZCNT64rm:
241  case X86::POPCNT16rm:
242  case X86::POPCNT32rm:
243  case X86::POPCNT64rm:
244  case X86::TZCNT16rm:
245  case X86::TZCNT32rm:
246  case X86::TZCNT64rm:
247 
248  // Bit manipulation instructions are effectively combinations of basic
249  // arithmetic ops, and should still execute in constant time. These also
250  // set flags.
251  case X86::BLCFILL32rm:
252  case X86::BLCFILL64rm:
253  case X86::BLCI32rm:
254  case X86::BLCI64rm:
255  case X86::BLCIC32rm:
256  case X86::BLCIC64rm:
257  case X86::BLCMSK32rm:
258  case X86::BLCMSK64rm:
259  case X86::BLCS32rm:
260  case X86::BLCS64rm:
261  case X86::BLSFILL32rm:
262  case X86::BLSFILL64rm:
263  case X86::BLSI32rm:
264  case X86::BLSI64rm:
265  case X86::BLSIC32rm:
266  case X86::BLSIC64rm:
267  case X86::BLSMSK32rm:
268  case X86::BLSMSK64rm:
269  case X86::BLSR32rm:
270  case X86::BLSR64rm:
271  case X86::TZMSK32rm:
272  case X86::TZMSK64rm:
273 
274  // Bit extracting and clearing instructions should execute in constant time,
275  // and set flags.
276  case X86::BEXTR32rm:
277  case X86::BEXTR64rm:
278  case X86::BEXTRI32mi:
279  case X86::BEXTRI64mi:
280  case X86::BZHI32rm:
281  case X86::BZHI64rm:
282 
283  // Basic arithmetic is constant time on the input but does set flags.
284  case X86::ADC8rm:
285  case X86::ADC16rm:
286  case X86::ADC32rm:
287  case X86::ADC64rm:
288  case X86::ADCX32rm:
289  case X86::ADCX64rm:
290  case X86::ADD8rm:
291  case X86::ADD16rm:
292  case X86::ADD32rm:
293  case X86::ADD64rm:
294  case X86::ADOX32rm:
295  case X86::ADOX64rm:
296  case X86::AND8rm:
297  case X86::AND16rm:
298  case X86::AND32rm:
299  case X86::AND64rm:
300  case X86::ANDN32rm:
301  case X86::ANDN64rm:
302  case X86::OR8rm:
303  case X86::OR16rm:
304  case X86::OR32rm:
305  case X86::OR64rm:
306  case X86::SBB8rm:
307  case X86::SBB16rm:
308  case X86::SBB32rm:
309  case X86::SBB64rm:
310  case X86::SUB8rm:
311  case X86::SUB16rm:
312  case X86::SUB32rm:
313  case X86::SUB64rm:
314  case X86::XOR8rm:
315  case X86::XOR16rm:
316  case X86::XOR32rm:
317  case X86::XOR64rm:
318 
319  // Integer multiply w/o affecting flags is still believed to be constant
320  // time on x86. Called out separately as this is among the most surprising
321  // instructions to exhibit that behavior.
322  case X86::MULX32rm:
323  case X86::MULX64rm:
324 
325  // Arithmetic instructions that are both constant time and don't set flags.
326  case X86::RORX32mi:
327  case X86::RORX64mi:
328  case X86::SARX32rm:
329  case X86::SARX64rm:
330  case X86::SHLX32rm:
331  case X86::SHLX64rm:
332  case X86::SHRX32rm:
333  case X86::SHRX64rm:
334 
335  // Conversions are believed to be constant time and don't set flags.
336  case X86::CVTTSD2SI64rm:
337  case X86::VCVTTSD2SI64rm:
338  case X86::VCVTTSD2SI64Zrm:
339  case X86::CVTTSD2SIrm:
340  case X86::VCVTTSD2SIrm:
341  case X86::VCVTTSD2SIZrm:
342  case X86::CVTTSS2SI64rm:
343  case X86::VCVTTSS2SI64rm:
344  case X86::VCVTTSS2SI64Zrm:
345  case X86::CVTTSS2SIrm:
346  case X86::VCVTTSS2SIrm:
347  case X86::VCVTTSS2SIZrm:
348  case X86::CVTSI2SDrm:
349  case X86::VCVTSI2SDrm:
350  case X86::VCVTSI2SDZrm:
351  case X86::CVTSI2SSrm:
352  case X86::VCVTSI2SSrm:
353  case X86::VCVTSI2SSZrm:
354  case X86::CVTSI642SDrm:
355  case X86::VCVTSI642SDrm:
356  case X86::VCVTSI642SDZrm:
357  case X86::CVTSI642SSrm:
358  case X86::VCVTSI642SSrm:
359  case X86::VCVTSI642SSZrm:
360  case X86::CVTSS2SDrm:
361  case X86::VCVTSS2SDrm:
362  case X86::VCVTSS2SDZrm:
363  case X86::CVTSD2SSrm:
364  case X86::VCVTSD2SSrm:
365  case X86::VCVTSD2SSZrm:
366  // AVX512 added unsigned integer conversions.
367  case X86::VCVTTSD2USI64Zrm:
368  case X86::VCVTTSD2USIZrm:
369  case X86::VCVTTSS2USI64Zrm:
370  case X86::VCVTTSS2USIZrm:
371  case X86::VCVTUSI2SDZrm:
372  case X86::VCVTUSI642SDZrm:
373  case X86::VCVTUSI2SSZrm:
374  case X86::VCVTUSI642SSZrm:
375 
376  // Loads to register don't set flags.
377  case X86::MOV8rm:
378  case X86::MOV8rm_NOREX:
379  case X86::MOV16rm:
380  case X86::MOV32rm:
381  case X86::MOV64rm:
382  case X86::MOVSX16rm8:
383  case X86::MOVSX32rm16:
384  case X86::MOVSX32rm8:
385  case X86::MOVSX32rm8_NOREX:
386  case X86::MOVSX64rm16:
387  case X86::MOVSX64rm32:
388  case X86::MOVSX64rm8:
389  case X86::MOVZX16rm8:
390  case X86::MOVZX32rm16:
391  case X86::MOVZX32rm8:
392  case X86::MOVZX32rm8_NOREX:
393  case X86::MOVZX64rm16:
394  case X86::MOVZX64rm8:
395  return true;
396  }
397 }

399 int X86InstrInfo::getSPAdjust(const MachineInstr &MI) const {
400  const MachineFunction *MF = MI.getParent()->getParent();
401  const TargetFrameLowering *TFI = MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering();
402 
403  if (isFrameInstr(MI)) {
404  int SPAdj = alignTo(getFrameSize(MI), TFI->getStackAlign());
405  SPAdj -= getFrameAdjustment(MI);
406  if (!isFrameSetup(MI))
407  SPAdj = -SPAdj;
408  return SPAdj;
409  }
410 
411  // To know whether a call adjusts the stack, we need information
412  // that is bound to the following ADJCALLSTACKUP pseudo.
413  // Look for the next ADJCALLSTACKUP that follows the call.
414  if (MI.isCall()) {
415  const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent();
416  auto I = ++MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator(MI);
417  for (auto E = MBB->end(); I != E; ++I) {
418  if (I->getOpcode() == getCallFrameDestroyOpcode() ||
419  I->isCall())
420  break;
421  }
422 
423  // If we could not find a frame destroy opcode, then it has already
424  // been simplified, so we don't care.
425  if (I->getOpcode() != getCallFrameDestroyOpcode())
426  return 0;
427 
428  return -(I->getOperand(1).getImm());
429  }
430 
431  // Currently handle only PUSHes we can reasonably expect to see
432  // in call sequences
433  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
434  default:
435  return 0;
436  case X86::PUSH32i8:
437  case X86::PUSH32r:
438  case X86::PUSH32rmm:
439  case X86::PUSH32rmr:
440  case X86::PUSHi32:
441  return 4;
442  case X86::PUSH64i8:
443  case X86::PUSH64r:
444  case X86::PUSH64rmm:
445  case X86::PUSH64rmr:
446  case X86::PUSH64i32:
447  return 8;
448  }
449 }
450 
451 /// Return true and the FrameIndex if the specified
452 /// operand and follow operands form a reference to the stack frame.
453 bool X86InstrInfo::isFrameOperand(const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned int Op,
454  int &FrameIndex) const {
455  if (MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrBaseReg).isFI() &&
456  MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrScaleAmt).isImm() &&
457  MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrIndexReg).isReg() &&
458  MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrDisp).isImm() &&
459  MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrScaleAmt).getImm() == 1 &&
460  MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrIndexReg).getReg() == 0 &&
461  MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrDisp).getImm() == 0) {
462  FrameIndex = MI.getOperand(Op + X86::AddrBaseReg).getIndex();
463  return true;
464  }
465  return false;
466 }

468 static bool isFrameLoadOpcode(int Opcode, unsigned &MemBytes) {
469  switch (Opcode) {
470  default:
471  return false;
472  case X86::MOV8rm:
473  case X86::KMOVBkm:
474  MemBytes = 1;
475  return true;
476  case X86::MOV16rm:
477  case X86::KMOVWkm:
478  case X86::VMOVSHZrm:
479  case X86::VMOVSHZrm_alt:
480  MemBytes = 2;
481  return true;
482  case X86::MOV32rm:
483  case X86::MOVSSrm:
484  case X86::MOVSSrm_alt:
485  case X86::VMOVSSrm:
486  case X86::VMOVSSrm_alt:
487  case X86::VMOVSSZrm:
488  case X86::VMOVSSZrm_alt:
489  case X86::KMOVDkm:
490  MemBytes = 4;
491  return true;
492  case X86::MOV64rm:
493  case X86::LD_Fp64m:
494  case X86::MOVSDrm:
495  case X86::MOVSDrm_alt:
496  case X86::VMOVSDrm:
497  case X86::VMOVSDrm_alt:
498  case X86::VMOVSDZrm:
499  case X86::VMOVSDZrm_alt:
500  case X86::MMX_MOVD64rm:
501  case X86::MMX_MOVQ64rm:
502  case X86::KMOVQkm:
503  MemBytes = 8;
504  return true;
505  case X86::MOVAPSrm:
506  case X86::MOVUPSrm:
507  case X86::MOVAPDrm:
508  case X86::MOVUPDrm:
509  case X86::MOVDQArm:
510  case X86::MOVDQUrm:
511  case X86::VMOVAPSrm:
512  case X86::VMOVUPSrm:
513  case X86::VMOVAPDrm:
514  case X86::VMOVUPDrm:
515  case X86::VMOVDQArm:
516  case X86::VMOVDQUrm:
517  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rm:
518  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rm:
519  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rm_NOVLX:
520  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rm_NOVLX:
521  case X86::VMOVAPDZ128rm:
522  case X86::VMOVUPDZ128rm:
523  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z128rm:
524  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z128rm:
525  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z128rm:
526  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z128rm:
527  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z128rm:
528  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z128rm:
529  MemBytes = 16;
530  return true;
531  case X86::VMOVAPSYrm:
532  case X86::VMOVUPSYrm:
533  case X86::VMOVAPDYrm:
534  case X86::VMOVUPDYrm:
535  case X86::VMOVDQAYrm:
536  case X86::VMOVDQUYrm:
537  case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rm:
538  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rm:
539  case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rm_NOVLX:
540  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rm_NOVLX:
541  case X86::VMOVAPDZ256rm:
542  case X86::VMOVUPDZ256rm:
543  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z256rm:
544  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z256rm:
545  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z256rm:
546  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z256rm:
547  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z256rm:
548  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z256rm:
549  MemBytes = 32;
550  return true;
551  case X86::VMOVAPSZrm:
552  case X86::VMOVUPSZrm:
553  case X86::VMOVAPDZrm:
554  case X86::VMOVUPDZrm:
555  case X86::VMOVDQU8Zrm:
556  case X86::VMOVDQU16Zrm:
557  case X86::VMOVDQA32Zrm:
558  case X86::VMOVDQU32Zrm:
559  case X86::VMOVDQA64Zrm:
560  case X86::VMOVDQU64Zrm:
561  MemBytes = 64;
562  return true;
563  }
564 }

566 static bool isFrameStoreOpcode(int Opcode, unsigned &MemBytes) {
567  switch (Opcode) {
568  default:
569  return false;
570  case X86::MOV8mr:
571  case X86::KMOVBmk:
572  MemBytes = 1;
573  return true;
574  case X86::MOV16mr:
575  case X86::KMOVWmk:
576  case X86::VMOVSHZmr:
577  MemBytes = 2;
578  return true;
579  case X86::MOV32mr:
580  case X86::MOVSSmr:
581  case X86::VMOVSSmr:
582  case X86::VMOVSSZmr:
583  case X86::KMOVDmk:
584  MemBytes = 4;
585  return true;
586  case X86::MOV64mr:
587  case X86::ST_FpP64m:
588  case X86::MOVSDmr:
589  case X86::VMOVSDmr:
590  case X86::VMOVSDZmr:
591  case X86::MMX_MOVD64mr:
592  case X86::MMX_MOVQ64mr:
593  case X86::MMX_MOVNTQmr:
594  case X86::KMOVQmk:
595  MemBytes = 8;
596  return true;
597  case X86::MOVAPSmr:
598  case X86::MOVUPSmr:
599  case X86::MOVAPDmr:
600  case X86::MOVUPDmr:
601  case X86::MOVDQAmr:
602  case X86::MOVDQUmr:
603  case X86::VMOVAPSmr:
604  case X86::VMOVUPSmr:
605  case X86::VMOVAPDmr:
606  case X86::VMOVUPDmr:
607  case X86::VMOVDQAmr:
608  case X86::VMOVDQUmr:
609  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128mr:
610  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128mr:
611  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128mr_NOVLX:
612  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128mr_NOVLX:
613  case X86::VMOVUPDZ128mr:
614  case X86::VMOVAPDZ128mr:
615  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z128mr:
616  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z128mr:
617  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z128mr:
618  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z128mr:
619  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z128mr:
620  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z128mr:

622  return true;
623  case X86::VMOVUPSYmr:
624  case X86::VMOVAPSYmr:

626  case X86::VMOVAPDYmr:
627  case X86::VMOVDQUYmr:
628  case X86::VMOVDQAYmr:
629  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256mr:
630  case X86::VMOVAPSZ256mr:
631  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256mr_NOVLX:

633  case X86::VMOVUPDZ256mr:

638  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z256mr:
639  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z256mr:
640  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z256mr:

642  return true;
643  case X86::VMOVUPSZmr:

645  case X86::VMOVUPDZmr:

647  case X86::VMOVDQU8Zmr:

650  case X86::VMOVDQU32Zmr:
651  case X86::VMOVDQA64Zmr:

654  return true;

659 unsigned X86InstrInfo::isLoadFromStackSlot(const MachineInstr &MI,
660  int &FrameIndex) const {
661  unsigned Dummy;
662  return X86InstrInfo::isLoadFromStackSlot(MI, FrameIndex, Dummy);
663 }
664 
665 unsigned X86InstrInfo::isLoadFromStackSlot(const MachineInstr &MI,
666  int &FrameIndex,
667  unsigned &MemBytes) const {
668  if (isFrameLoadOpcode(MI.getOpcode(), MemBytes))
669  if (MI.getOperand(0).getSubReg() == 0 && isFrameOperand(MI, 1, FrameIndex))
670  return MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
671  return 0;
672 }
673 
674 unsigned X86InstrInfo::isLoadFromStackSlotPostFE(const MachineInstr &MI,
675  int &FrameIndex) const {
676  unsigned Dummy;
677  if (isFrameLoadOpcode(MI.getOpcode(), Dummy)) {
678  unsigned Reg;
679  if ((Reg = isLoadFromStackSlot(MI, FrameIndex)))
680  return Reg;
681  // Check for post-frame index elimination operations
682  SmallVector<const MachineMemOperand *, 1> Accesses;
683  if (hasLoadFromStackSlot(MI, Accesses)) {
684  FrameIndex =
685  cast<FixedStackPseudoSourceValue>(Accesses.front()->getPseudoValue())
686  ->getFrameIndex();
687  return MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
688  }
689  }
690  return 0;
691 }

693 unsigned X86InstrInfo::isStoreToStackSlot(const MachineInstr &MI,
694  int &FrameIndex) const {
695  unsigned Dummy;
696  return X86InstrInfo::isStoreToStackSlot(MI, FrameIndex, Dummy);
697 }
698 
699 unsigned X86InstrInfo::isStoreToStackSlot(const MachineInstr &MI,
700  int &FrameIndex,
701  unsigned &MemBytes) const {
702  if (isFrameStoreOpcode(MI.getOpcode(), MemBytes))
703  if (MI.getOperand(X86::AddrNumOperands).getSubReg() == 0 &&
704  isFrameOperand(MI, 0, FrameIndex))
705  return MI.getOperand(X86::AddrNumOperands).getReg();
706  return 0;
707 }
708 
709 unsigned X86InstrInfo::isStoreToStackSlotPostFE(const MachineInstr &MI,
710  int &FrameIndex) const {
711  unsigned Dummy;
712  if (isFrameStoreOpcode(MI.getOpcode(), Dummy)) {
713  unsigned Reg;
714  if ((Reg = isStoreToStackSlot(MI, FrameIndex)))
715  return Reg;
716  // Check for post-frame index elimination operations
717  SmallVector<const MachineMemOperand *, 1> Accesses;
718  if (hasStoreToStackSlot(MI, Accesses)) {
719  FrameIndex =
720  cast<FixedStackPseudoSourceValue>(Accesses.front()->getPseudoValue())
721  ->getFrameIndex();
722  return MI.getOperand(X86::AddrNumOperands).getReg();
723  }
724  }
725  return 0;
726 }
727 
728 /// Return true if register is PIC base; i.e.g defined by X86::MOVPC32r.
729 static bool regIsPICBase(Register BaseReg, const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) {
730  // Don't waste compile time scanning use-def chains of physregs.
731  if (!BaseReg.isVirtual())
732  return false;
733  bool isPICBase = false;
734  for (MachineRegisterInfo::def_instr_iterator I = MRI.def_instr_begin(BaseReg),
735  E = MRI.def_instr_end(); I != E; ++I) {
736  MachineInstr *DefMI = &*I;
737  if (DefMI->getOpcode() != X86::MOVPC32r)
738  return false;
739  assert(!isPICBase && "More than one PIC base?");
740  isPICBase = true;
741  }
742  return isPICBase;
743 }

745 bool X86InstrInfo::isReallyTriviallyReMaterializable(
746  const MachineInstr &MI) const {
747  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
748  default:
749  // This function should only be called for opcodes with the ReMaterializable
750  // flag set.
751  llvm_unreachable("Unknown rematerializable operation!");
752  break;
753 
754  case X86::LOAD_STACK_GUARD:
755  case X86::AVX1_SETALLONES:
756  case X86::AVX2_SETALLONES:
757  case X86::AVX512_128_SET0:
758  case X86::AVX512_256_SET0:
759  case X86::AVX512_512_SET0:
760  case X86::AVX512_512_SETALLONES:
761  case X86::AVX512_FsFLD0SD:
762  case X86::AVX512_FsFLD0SH:
763  case X86::AVX512_FsFLD0SS:
764  case X86::AVX512_FsFLD0F128:
765  case X86::AVX_SET0:
766  case X86::FsFLD0SD:
767  case X86::FsFLD0SS:
768  case X86::FsFLD0SH:
769  case X86::FsFLD0F128:
770  case X86::KSET0D:
771  case X86::KSET0Q:
772  case X86::KSET0W:
773  case X86::KSET1D:
774  case X86::KSET1Q:
775  case X86::KSET1W:
776  case X86::MMX_SET0:
777  case X86::MOV32ImmSExti8:
778  case X86::MOV32r0:
779  case X86::MOV32r1:
780  case X86::MOV32r_1:
781  case X86::MOV32ri64:
782  case X86::MOV64ImmSExti8:
783  case X86::V_SET0:
784  case X86::V_SETALLONES:
785  case X86::MOV16ri:
786  case X86::MOV32ri:
787  case X86::MOV64ri:
788  case X86::MOV64ri32:
789  case X86::MOV8ri:
790  case X86::PTILEZEROV:
791  return true;
792 
793  case X86::MOV8rm:
794  case X86::MOV8rm_NOREX:
795  case X86::MOV16rm:
796  case X86::MOV32rm:
797  case X86::MOV64rm:
798  case X86::MOVSSrm:
799  case X86::MOVSSrm_alt:
800  case X86::MOVSDrm:
801  case X86::MOVSDrm_alt:
802  case X86::MOVAPSrm:
803  case X86::MOVUPSrm:
804  case X86::MOVAPDrm:
805  case X86::MOVUPDrm:
806  case X86::MOVDQArm:
807  case X86::MOVDQUrm:
808  case X86::VMOVSSrm:
809  case X86::VMOVSSrm_alt:
810  case X86::VMOVSDrm:
811  case X86::VMOVSDrm_alt:
812  case X86::VMOVAPSrm:
813  case X86::VMOVUPSrm:
814  case X86::VMOVAPDrm:
815  case X86::VMOVUPDrm:
816  case X86::VMOVDQArm:
817  case X86::VMOVDQUrm:
818  case X86::VMOVAPSYrm:
819  case X86::VMOVUPSYrm:
820  case X86::VMOVAPDYrm:
821  case X86::VMOVUPDYrm:
822  case X86::VMOVDQAYrm:
823  case X86::VMOVDQUYrm:
824  case X86::MMX_MOVD64rm:
825  case X86::MMX_MOVQ64rm:
826  // AVX-512
827  case X86::VMOVSSZrm:
828  case X86::VMOVSSZrm_alt:
829  case X86::VMOVSDZrm:
830  case X86::VMOVSDZrm_alt:
831  case X86::VMOVSHZrm:
832  case X86::VMOVSHZrm_alt:
833  case X86::VMOVAPDZ128rm:
834  case X86::VMOVAPDZ256rm:
835  case X86::VMOVAPDZrm:
836  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rm:
837  case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rm:
838  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rm_NOVLX:
839  case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rm_NOVLX:
840  case X86::VMOVAPSZrm:
841  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z128rm:
842  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z256rm:
843  case X86::VMOVDQA32Zrm:
844  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z128rm:
845  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z256rm:
846  case X86::VMOVDQA64Zrm:
847  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z128rm:
848  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z256rm:
849  case X86::VMOVDQU16Zrm:
850  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z128rm:
851  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z256rm:
852  case X86::VMOVDQU32Zrm:
853  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z128rm:
854  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z256rm:
855  case X86::VMOVDQU64Zrm:
856  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z128rm:
857  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z256rm:
858  case X86::VMOVDQU8Zrm:
859  case X86::VMOVUPDZ128rm:
860  case X86::VMOVUPDZ256rm:
861  case X86::VMOVUPDZrm:
862  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rm:
863  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rm:
864  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rm_NOVLX:
865  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rm_NOVLX:
866  case X86::VMOVUPSZrm: {
867  // Loads from constant pools are trivially rematerializable.
868  if (MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrBaseReg).isReg() &&
869  MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrScaleAmt).isImm() &&
870  MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrIndexReg).isReg() &&
871  MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrIndexReg).getReg() == 0 &&
872  MI.isDereferenceableInvariantLoad()) {
873  Register BaseReg = MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrBaseReg).getReg();
874  if (BaseReg == 0 || BaseReg == X86::RIP)
875  return true;
876  // Allow re-materialization of PIC load.
877  if (!ReMatPICStubLoad && MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrDisp).isGlobal())
878  return false;
879  const MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent();
880  const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
881  return regIsPICBase(BaseReg, MRI);
882  }
883  return false;
884  }
885 
886  case X86::LEA32r:
887  case X86::LEA64r: {
888  if (MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrScaleAmt).isImm() &&
889  MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrIndexReg).isReg() &&
890  MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrIndexReg).getReg() == 0 &&
891  !MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrDisp).isReg()) {
892  // lea fi#, lea GV, etc. are all rematerializable.
893  if (!MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrBaseReg).isReg())
894  return true;
895  Register BaseReg = MI.getOperand(1 + X86::AddrBaseReg).getReg();
896  if (BaseReg == 0)
897  return true;
898  // Allow re-materialization of lea PICBase + x.
899  const MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent();
900  const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
901  return regIsPICBase(BaseReg, MRI);
902  }
903  return false;
904  }
905  }
906 }
907 
908 void X86InstrInfo::reMaterialize(MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
909  MachineBasicBlock::iterator I,
910  Register DestReg, unsigned SubIdx,
911  const MachineInstr &Orig,
912  const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI) const {
913  bool ClobbersEFLAGS = Orig.modifiesRegister(X86::EFLAGS, &TRI);
914  if (ClobbersEFLAGS && MBB.computeRegisterLiveness(&TRI, X86::EFLAGS, I) !=
915  MachineBasicBlock::LQR_Dead) {
916  // The instruction clobbers EFLAGS. Re-materialize as MOV32ri to avoid side
917  // effects.
918  int Value;
919  switch (Orig.getOpcode()) {
920  case X86::MOV32r0: Value = 0; break;
921  case X86::MOV32r1: Value = 1; break;
922  case X86::MOV32r_1: Value = -1; break;
923  default:
924  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected instruction!");
925  }
926 
927  const DebugLoc &DL = Orig.getDebugLoc();
928  BuildMI(MBB, I, DL, get(X86::MOV32ri))
929  .add(Orig.getOperand(0))
930  .addImm(Value);
931  } else {
932  MachineInstr *MI = MBB.getParent()->CloneMachineInstr(&Orig);
933  MBB.insert(I, MI);
934  }
935 
936  MachineInstr &NewMI = *std::prev(I);
937  NewMI.substituteRegister(Orig.getOperand(0).getReg(), DestReg, SubIdx, TRI);
938 }
939 
940 /// True if MI has a condition code def, e.g. EFLAGS, that is not marked dead.
941 bool X86InstrInfo::hasLiveCondCodeDef(MachineInstr &MI) const {
942  for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) {
943  if (MO.isReg() && MO.isDef() &&
944  MO.getReg() == X86::EFLAGS && !MO.isDead()) {
945  return true;
946  }
947  }
948  return false;
949 }
950 
951 /// Check whether the shift count for a machine operand is non-zero.
952 inline static unsigned getTruncatedShiftCount(const MachineInstr &MI,
953  unsigned ShiftAmtOperandIdx) {
954  // The shift count is six bits with the REX.W prefix and five bits without.
955  unsigned ShiftCountMask = (MI.getDesc().TSFlags & X86II::REX_W) ? 63 : 31;
956  unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(ShiftAmtOperandIdx).getImm();
957  return Imm & ShiftCountMask;
958 }
959 
960 /// Check whether the given shift count is appropriate
961 /// can be represented by a LEA instruction.
962 inline static bool isTruncatedShiftCountForLEA(unsigned ShAmt) {
963  // Left shift instructions can be transformed into load-effective-address
964  // instructions if we can encode them appropriately.
965  // A LEA instruction utilizes a SIB byte to encode its scale factor.
966  // The SIB.scale field is two bits wide which means that we can encode any
967  // shift amount less than 4.
968  return ShAmt < 4 && ShAmt > 0;
969 }
970 
971 static bool findRedundantFlagInstr(MachineInstr &CmpInstr,
972  MachineInstr &CmpValDefInstr,
973  const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI,
974  MachineInstr **AndInstr,
975  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
976  bool &NoSignFlag, bool &ClearsOverflowFlag) {
977  if (CmpValDefInstr.getOpcode() != X86::SUBREG_TO_REG)
978  return false;
979 
980  if (CmpInstr.getOpcode() != X86::TEST64rr)
981  return false;
982 
983  // CmpInstr is a TEST64rr instruction, and `X86InstrInfo::analyzeCompare`
984  // guarantees that it's analyzable only if two registers are identical.
985  assert(
986  (CmpInstr.getOperand(0).getReg() == CmpInstr.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
987  "CmpInstr is an analyzable TEST64rr, and `X86InstrInfo::analyzeCompare` "
988  "requires two reg operands are the same.");
989 
990  // Caller (`X86InstrInfo::optimizeCompareInstr`) guarantees that
991  // `CmpValDefInstr` defines the value that's used by `CmpInstr`; in this case
992  // if `CmpValDefInstr` sets the EFLAGS, it is likely that `CmpInstr` is
993  // redundant.
994  assert(
995  (MRI->getVRegDef(CmpInstr.getOperand(0).getReg()) == &CmpValDefInstr) &&
996  "Caller guarantees that TEST64rr is a user of SUBREG_TO_REG.");
997 
998  // As seen in X86 td files, CmpValDefInstr.getOperand(1).getImm() is typically
999  // 0.
1000  if (CmpValDefInstr.getOperand(1).getImm() != 0)
1001  return false;
1002 
1003  // As seen in X86 td files, CmpValDefInstr.getOperand(3) is typically
1004  // sub_32bit or sub_xmm.
1005  if (CmpValDefInstr.getOperand(3).getImm() != X86::sub_32bit)
1006  return false;
1007 
1008  MachineInstr *VregDefInstr =
1009  MRI->getVRegDef(CmpValDefInstr.getOperand(2).getReg());
1010 
1011  assert(VregDefInstr && "Must have a definition (SSA)");
1012 
1013  // Requires `CmpValDefInstr` and `VregDefInstr` are from the same MBB
1014  // to simplify the subsequent analysis.
1015  //
1016  // FIXME: If `VregDefInstr->getParent()` is the only predecessor of
1017  // `CmpValDefInstr.getParent()`, this could be handled.
1018  if (VregDefInstr->getParent() != CmpValDefInstr.getParent())
1019  return false;
1020 
1021  if (X86::isAND(VregDefInstr->getOpcode())) {
1022  // Get a sequence of instructions like
1023  // %reg = and* ... // Set EFLAGS
1024  // ... // EFLAGS not changed
1025  // %extended_reg = subreg_to_reg 0, %reg, %subreg.sub_32bit
1026  // test64rr %extended_reg, %extended_reg, implicit-def $eflags
1027  //
1028  // If subsequent readers use a subset of bits that don't change
1029  // after `and*` instructions, it's likely that the test64rr could
1030  // be optimized away.
1031  for (const MachineInstr &Instr :
1032  make_range(std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(VregDefInstr)),
1033  MachineBasicBlock::iterator(CmpValDefInstr))) {
1034  // There are instructions between 'VregDefInstr' and
1035  // 'CmpValDefInstr' that modifies EFLAGS.
1036  if (Instr.modifiesRegister(X86::EFLAGS, TRI))
1037  return false;
1038  }
1039 
1040  *AndInstr = VregDefInstr;
1041 
1042  // AND instruction will essentially update SF and clear OF, so
1043  // NoSignFlag should be false in the sense that SF is modified by `AND`.
1044  //
1045  // However, the implementation artifically sets `NoSignFlag` to true
1046  // to poison the SF bit; that is to say, if SF is looked at later, the
1047  // optimization (to erase TEST64rr) will be disabled.
1048  //
1049  // The reason to poison SF bit is that SF bit value could be different
1050  // in the `AND` and `TEST` operation; signed bit is not known for `AND`,
1051  // and is known to be 0 as a result of `TEST64rr`.
1052  //
1053  // FIXME: As opposed to poisoning the SF bit directly, consider peeking into
1054  // the AND instruction and using the static information to guide peephole
1055  // optimization if possible. For example, it's possible to fold a
1056  // conditional move into a copy if the relevant EFLAG bits could be deduced
1057  // from an immediate operand of and operation.
1058  //
1059  NoSignFlag = true;
1060  // ClearsOverflowFlag is true for AND operation (no surprise).
1061  ClearsOverflowFlag = true;
1062  return true;
1063  }
1064  return false;
1065 }
1066 
1067 bool X86InstrInfo::classifyLEAReg(MachineInstr &MI, const MachineOperand &Src,
1068  unsigned Opc, bool AllowSP, Register &NewSrc,
1069  bool &isKill, MachineOperand &ImplicitOp,
1070  LiveVariables *LV, LiveIntervals *LIS) const {
1071  MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent();
1072  const TargetRegisterClass *RC;
1073  if (AllowSP) {
1074  RC = Opc != X86::LEA32r ? &X86::GR64RegClass : &X86::GR32RegClass;
1075  } else {
1076  RC = Opc != X86::LEA32r ?
1077  &X86::GR64_NOSPRegClass : &X86::GR32_NOSPRegClass;
1078  }
1079  Register SrcReg = Src.getReg();
1080  isKill = MI.killsRegister(SrcReg);
1081 
1082  // For both LEA64 and LEA32 the register already has essentially the right
1083  // type (32-bit or 64-bit) we may just need to forbid SP.
1084  if (Opc != X86::LEA64_32r) {
1085  NewSrc = SrcReg;
1086  assert(!Src.isUndef() && "Undef op doesn't need optimization");
1087 
1088  if (NewSrc.isVirtual() && !MF.getRegInfo().constrainRegClass(NewSrc, RC))
1089  return false;
1090 
1091  return true;
1092  }
1093 
1094  // This is for an LEA64_32r and incoming registers are 32-bit. One way or
1095  // another we need to add 64-bit registers to the final MI.
1096  if (SrcReg.isPhysical()) {
1097  ImplicitOp = Src;
1098  ImplicitOp.setImplicit();
1099 
1100  NewSrc = getX86SubSuperRegister(SrcReg, 64);
1101  assert(NewSrc.isValid() && "Invalid Operand");
1102  assert(!Src.isUndef() && "Undef op doesn't need optimization");
1103  } else {
1104  // Virtual register of the wrong class, we have to create a temporary 64-bit
1105  // vreg to feed into the LEA.
1106  NewSrc = MF.getRegInfo().createVirtualRegister(RC);
1107  MachineInstr *Copy =
1108  BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(TargetOpcode::COPY))
1109  .addReg(NewSrc, RegState::Define | RegState::Undef, X86::sub_32bit)
1110  .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(isKill));
1111 
1112  // Which is obviously going to be dead after we're done with it.
1113  isKill = true;
1114 
1115  if (LV)
1116  LV->replaceKillInstruction(SrcReg, MI, *Copy);
1117 
1118  if (LIS) {
1119  SlotIndex CopyIdx = LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*Copy);
1120  SlotIndex Idx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(MI);
1121  LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(SrcReg);
1122  LiveRange::Segment *S = LI.getSegmentContaining(Idx);
1123  if (S->end.getBaseIndex() == Idx)
1124  S->end = CopyIdx.getRegSlot();
1125  }
1126  }
1127 
1128  // We've set all the parameters without issue.
1129  return true;
1130 }
1131 
1132 MachineInstr *X86InstrInfo::convertToThreeAddressWithLEA(unsigned MIOpc,
1133  MachineInstr &MI,
1134  LiveVariables *LV,
1135  LiveIntervals *LIS,
1136  bool Is8BitOp) const {
1137  // We handle 8-bit adds and various 16-bit opcodes in the switch below.
1138  MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent();
1139  MachineRegisterInfo &RegInfo = MBB.getParent()->getRegInfo();
1140  assert((Is8BitOp || RegInfo.getTargetRegisterInfo()->getRegSizeInBits(
1141  *RegInfo.getRegClass(MI.getOperand(0).getReg())) == 16) &&
1142  "Unexpected type for LEA transform");
1143 
1144  // TODO: For a 32-bit target, we need to adjust the LEA variables with
1145  // something like this:
1146  // Opcode = X86::LEA32r;
1147  // InRegLEA = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&X86::GR32_NOSPRegClass);
1148  // OutRegLEA =
1149  // Is8BitOp ? RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&X86::GR32ABCD_RegClass)
1150  // : RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&X86::GR32RegClass);
1151  if (!Subtarget.is64Bit())
1152  return nullptr;
1153 
1154  unsigned Opcode = X86::LEA64_32r;
1155  Register InRegLEA = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&X86::GR64_NOSPRegClass);
1156  Register OutRegLEA = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&X86::GR32RegClass);
1157  Register InRegLEA2;
1158 
1159  // Build and insert into an implicit UNDEF value. This is OK because
1160  // we will be shifting and then extracting the lower 8/16-bits.
1161  // This has the potential to cause partial register stall. e.g.
1162  // movw (%rbp,%rcx,2), %dx
1163  // leal -65(%rdx), %esi
1164  // But testing has shown this *does* help performance in 64-bit mode (at
1165  // least on modern x86 machines).
1166  MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MI.getIterator();
1167  Register Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
1168  Register Src = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
1169  Register Src2;
1170  bool IsDead = MI.getOperand(0).isDead();
1171  bool IsKill = MI.getOperand(1).isKill();
1172  unsigned SubReg = Is8BitOp ? X86::sub_8bit : X86::sub_16bit;
1173  assert(!MI.getOperand(1).isUndef() && "Undef op doesn't need optimization");
1174  MachineInstr *ImpDef =
1175  BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(X86::IMPLICIT_DEF), InRegLEA);
1176  MachineInstr *InsMI =
1177  BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(TargetOpcode::COPY))
1178  .addReg(InRegLEA, RegState::Define, SubReg)
1179  .addReg(Src, getKillRegState(IsKill));
1180  MachineInstr *ImpDef2 = nullptr;
1181  MachineInstr *InsMI2 = nullptr;
1182 
1183  MachineInstrBuilder MIB =
1184  BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opcode), OutRegLEA);
1185  switch (MIOpc) {
1186  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
1187  case X86::SHL8ri:
1188  case X86::SHL16ri: {
1189  unsigned ShAmt = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
1190  MIB.addReg(0)
1191  .addImm(1LL << ShAmt)
1192  .addReg(InRegLEA, RegState::Kill)
1193  .addImm(0)
1194  .addReg(0);
1195  break;
1196  }
1197  case X86::INC8r:
1198  case X86::INC16r:
1199  addRegOffset(MIB, InRegLEA, true, 1);
1200  break;
1201  case X86::DEC8r:
1202  case X86::DEC16r:
1203  addRegOffset(MIB, InRegLEA, true, -1);
1204  break;
1205  case X86::ADD8ri:
1206  case X86::ADD8ri_DB:
1207  case X86::ADD16ri:
1208  case X86::ADD16ri8:
1209  case X86::ADD16ri_DB:
1210  case X86::ADD16ri8_DB:
1211  addRegOffset(MIB, InRegLEA, true, MI.getOperand(2).getImm());
1212  break;
1213  case X86::ADD8rr:
1214  case X86::ADD8rr_DB:
1215  case X86::ADD16rr:
1216  case X86::ADD16rr_DB: {
1217  Src2 = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
1218  bool IsKill2 = MI.getOperand(2).isKill();
1219  assert(!MI.getOperand(2).isUndef() && "Undef op doesn't need optimization");
1220  if (Src == Src2) {
1221  // ADD8rr/ADD16rr killed %reg1028, %reg1028
1222  // just a single insert_subreg.
1223  addRegReg(MIB, InRegLEA, true, InRegLEA, false);
1224  } else {
1225  if (Subtarget.is64Bit())
1226  InRegLEA2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&X86::GR64_NOSPRegClass);
1227  else
1228  InRegLEA2 = RegInfo.createVirtualRegister(&X86::GR32_NOSPRegClass);
1229  // Build and insert into an implicit UNDEF value. This is OK because
1230  // we will be shifting and then extracting the lower 8/16-bits.
1231  ImpDef2 = BuildMI(MBB, &*MIB, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(X86::IMPLICIT_DEF),
1232  InRegLEA2);
1233  InsMI2 = BuildMI(MBB, &*MIB, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(TargetOpcode::COPY))
1234  .addReg(InRegLEA2, RegState::Define, SubReg)
1235  .addReg(Src2, getKillRegState(IsKill2));
1236  addRegReg(MIB, InRegLEA, true, InRegLEA2, true);
1237  }
1238  if (LV && IsKill2 && InsMI2)
1239  LV->replaceKillInstruction(Src2, MI, *InsMI2);
1240  break;
1241  }
1242  }
1243 
1244  MachineInstr *NewMI = MIB;
1245  MachineInstr *ExtMI =
1246  BuildMI(MBB, MBBI, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(TargetOpcode::COPY))
1247  .addReg(Dest, RegState::Define | getDeadRegState(IsDead))
1248  .addReg(OutRegLEA, RegState::Kill, SubReg);
1249 
1250  if (LV) {
1251  // Update live variables.
1252  LV->getVarInfo(InRegLEA).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1253  if (InRegLEA2)
1254  LV->getVarInfo(InRegLEA2).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1255  LV->getVarInfo(OutRegLEA).Kills.push_back(ExtMI);
1256  if (IsKill)
1257  LV->replaceKillInstruction(Src, MI, *InsMI);
1258  if (IsDead)
1259  LV->replaceKillInstruction(Dest, MI, *ExtMI);
1260  }
1261 
1262  if (LIS) {
1263  LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*ImpDef);
1264  SlotIndex InsIdx = LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*InsMI);
1265  if (ImpDef2)
1266  LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*ImpDef2);
1267  SlotIndex Ins2Idx;
1268  if (InsMI2)
1269  Ins2Idx = LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*InsMI2);
1270  SlotIndex NewIdx = LIS->ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(MI, *NewMI);
1271  SlotIndex ExtIdx = LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*ExtMI);
1272  LIS->getInterval(InRegLEA);
1273  LIS->getInterval(OutRegLEA);
1274  if (InRegLEA2)
1275  LIS->getInterval(InRegLEA2);
1276 
1277  // Move the use of Src up to InsMI.
1278  LiveInterval &SrcLI = LIS->getInterval(Src);
1279  LiveRange::Segment *SrcSeg = SrcLI.getSegmentContaining(NewIdx);
1280  if (SrcSeg->end == NewIdx.getRegSlot())
1281  SrcSeg->end = InsIdx.getRegSlot();
1282 
1283  if (InsMI2) {
1284  // Move the use of Src2 up to InsMI2.
1285  LiveInterval &Src2LI = LIS->getInterval(Src2);
1286  LiveRange::Segment *Src2Seg = Src2LI.getSegmentContaining(NewIdx);
1287  if (Src2Seg->end == NewIdx.getRegSlot())
1288  Src2Seg->end = Ins2Idx.getRegSlot();
1289  }
1290 
1291  // Move the definition of Dest down to ExtMI.
1292  LiveInterval &DestLI = LIS->getInterval(Dest);
1293  LiveRange::Segment *DestSeg =
1294  DestLI.getSegmentContaining(NewIdx.getRegSlot());
1295  assert(DestSeg->start == NewIdx.getRegSlot() &&
1296  DestSeg->valno->def == NewIdx.getRegSlot());
1297  DestSeg->start = ExtIdx.getRegSlot();
1298  DestSeg->valno->def = ExtIdx.getRegSlot();
1299  }
1300 
1301  return ExtMI;
1302 }
1303 
1304 /// This method must be implemented by targets that
1305 /// set the M_CONVERTIBLE_TO_3_ADDR flag. When this flag is set, the target
1306 /// may be able to convert a two-address instruction into a true
1307 /// three-address instruction on demand. This allows the X86 target (for
1308 /// example) to convert ADD and SHL instructions into LEA instructions if they
1309 /// would require register copies due to two-addressness.
1310 ///
1311 /// This method returns a null pointer if the transformation cannot be
1312 /// performed, otherwise it returns the new instruction.
1313 ///
1314 MachineInstr *X86InstrInfo::convertToThreeAddress(MachineInstr &MI,
1315  LiveVariables *LV,
1316  LiveIntervals *LIS) const {
1317  // The following opcodes also sets the condition code register(s). Only
1318  // convert them to equivalent lea if the condition code register def's
1319  // are dead!
1320  if (hasLiveCondCodeDef(MI))
1321  return nullptr;
1322 
1323  MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent();
1324  // All instructions input are two-addr instructions. Get the known operands.
1325  const MachineOperand &Dest = MI.getOperand(0);
1326  const MachineOperand &Src = MI.getOperand(1);
1327 
1328  // Ideally, operations with undef should be folded before we get here, but we
1329  // can't guarantee it. Bail out because optimizing undefs is a waste of time.
1330  // Without this, we have to forward undef state to new register operands to
1331  // avoid machine verifier errors.
1332  if (Src.isUndef())
1333  return nullptr;
1334  if (MI.getNumOperands() > 2)
1335  if (MI.getOperand(2).isReg() && MI.getOperand(2).isUndef())
1336  return nullptr;
1337 
1338  MachineInstr *NewMI = nullptr;
1339  Register SrcReg, SrcReg2;
1340  bool Is64Bit = Subtarget.is64Bit();
1341 
1342  bool Is8BitOp = false;
1343  unsigned NumRegOperands = 2;
1344  unsigned MIOpc = MI.getOpcode();
1345  switch (MIOpc) {
1346  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
1347  case X86::SHL64ri: {
1348  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown shift instruction!");
1349  unsigned ShAmt = getTruncatedShiftCount(MI, 2);
1350  if (!isTruncatedShiftCountForLEA(ShAmt)) return nullptr;
1351 
1352  // LEA can't handle RSP.
1353  if (Src.getReg().isVirtual() && !MF.getRegInfo().constrainRegClass(
1354  Src.getReg(), &X86::GR64_NOSPRegClass))
1355  return nullptr;
1356 
1357  NewMI = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(X86::LEA64r))
1358  .add(Dest)
1359  .addReg(0)
1360  .addImm(1LL << ShAmt)
1361  .add(Src)
1362  .addImm(0)
1363  .addReg(0);
1364  break;
1365  }
1366  case X86::SHL32ri: {
1367  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown shift instruction!");
1368  unsigned ShAmt = getTruncatedShiftCount(MI, 2);
1369  if (!isTruncatedShiftCountForLEA(ShAmt)) return nullptr;
1370 
1371  unsigned Opc = Is64Bit ? X86::LEA64_32r : X86::LEA32r;
1372 
1373  // LEA can't handle ESP.
1374  bool isKill;
1375  MachineOperand ImplicitOp = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0, false);
1376  if (!classifyLEAReg(MI, Src, Opc, /*AllowSP=*/false, SrcReg, isKill,
1377  ImplicitOp, LV, LIS))
1378  return nullptr;
1379 
1380  MachineInstrBuilder MIB =
1381  BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc))
1382  .add(Dest)
1383  .addReg(0)
1384  .addImm(1LL << ShAmt)
1385  .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(isKill))
1386  .addImm(0)
1387  .addReg(0);
1388  if (ImplicitOp.getReg() != 0)
1389  MIB.add(ImplicitOp);
1390  NewMI = MIB;
1391 
1392  // Add kills if classifyLEAReg created a new register.
1393  if (LV && SrcReg != Src.getReg())
1394  LV->getVarInfo(SrcReg).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1395  break;
1396  }
1397  case X86::SHL8ri:
1398  Is8BitOp = true;
1399  [[fallthrough]];
1400  case X86::SHL16ri: {
1401  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown shift instruction!");
1402  unsigned ShAmt = getTruncatedShiftCount(MI, 2);
1403  if (!isTruncatedShiftCountForLEA(ShAmt))
1404  return nullptr;
1405  return convertToThreeAddressWithLEA(MIOpc, MI, LV, LIS, Is8BitOp);
1406  }
1407  case X86::INC64r:
1408  case X86::INC32r: {
1409  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 2 && "Unknown inc instruction!");
1410  unsigned Opc = MIOpc == X86::INC64r ? X86::LEA64r :
1411  (Is64Bit ? X86::LEA64_32r : X86::LEA32r);
1412  bool isKill;
1413  MachineOperand ImplicitOp = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0, false);
1414  if (!classifyLEAReg(MI, Src, Opc, /*AllowSP=*/false, SrcReg, isKill,
1415  ImplicitOp, LV, LIS))
1416  return nullptr;
1417 
1418  MachineInstrBuilder MIB =
1419  BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc))
1420  .add(Dest)
1421  .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(isKill));
1422  if (ImplicitOp.getReg() != 0)
1423  MIB.add(ImplicitOp);
1424 
1425  NewMI = addOffset(MIB, 1);
1426 
1427  // Add kills if classifyLEAReg created a new register.
1428  if (LV && SrcReg != Src.getReg())
1429  LV->getVarInfo(SrcReg).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1430  break;
1431  }
1432  case X86::DEC64r:
1433  case X86::DEC32r: {
1434  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 2 && "Unknown dec instruction!");
1435  unsigned Opc = MIOpc == X86::DEC64r ? X86::LEA64r
1436  : (Is64Bit ? X86::LEA64_32r : X86::LEA32r);
1437 
1438  bool isKill;
1439  MachineOperand ImplicitOp = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0, false);
1440  if (!classifyLEAReg(MI, Src, Opc, /*AllowSP=*/false, SrcReg, isKill,
1441  ImplicitOp, LV, LIS))
1442  return nullptr;
1443 
1444  MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc))
1445  .add(Dest)
1446  .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(isKill));
1447  if (ImplicitOp.getReg() != 0)
1448  MIB.add(ImplicitOp);
1449 
1450  NewMI = addOffset(MIB, -1);
1451 
1452  // Add kills if classifyLEAReg created a new register.
1453  if (LV && SrcReg != Src.getReg())
1454  LV->getVarInfo(SrcReg).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1455  break;
1456  }
1457  case X86::DEC8r:
1458  case X86::INC8r:
1459  Is8BitOp = true;
1460  [[fallthrough]];
1461  case X86::DEC16r:
1462  case X86::INC16r:
1463  return convertToThreeAddressWithLEA(MIOpc, MI, LV, LIS, Is8BitOp);
1464  case X86::ADD64rr:
1465  case X86::ADD64rr_DB:
1466  case X86::ADD32rr:
1467  case X86::ADD32rr_DB: {
1468  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown add instruction!");
1469  unsigned Opc;
1470  if (MIOpc == X86::ADD64rr || MIOpc == X86::ADD64rr_DB)
1471  Opc = X86::LEA64r;
1472  else
1473  Opc = Is64Bit ? X86::LEA64_32r : X86::LEA32r;
1474 
1475  const MachineOperand &Src2 = MI.getOperand(2);
1476  bool isKill2;
1477  MachineOperand ImplicitOp2 = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0, false);
1478  if (!classifyLEAReg(MI, Src2, Opc, /*AllowSP=*/false, SrcReg2, isKill2,
1479  ImplicitOp2, LV, LIS))
1480  return nullptr;
1481 
1482  bool isKill;
1483  MachineOperand ImplicitOp = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0, false);
1484  if (Src.getReg() == Src2.getReg()) {
1485  // Don't call classify LEAReg a second time on the same register, in case
1486  // the first call inserted a COPY from Src2 and marked it as killed.
1487  isKill = isKill2;
1488  SrcReg = SrcReg2;
1489  } else {
1490  if (!classifyLEAReg(MI, Src, Opc, /*AllowSP=*/true, SrcReg, isKill,
1491  ImplicitOp, LV, LIS))
1492  return nullptr;
1493  }
1494 
1495  MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc)).add(Dest);
1496  if (ImplicitOp.getReg() != 0)
1497  MIB.add(ImplicitOp);
1498  if (ImplicitOp2.getReg() != 0)
1499  MIB.add(ImplicitOp2);
1500 
1501  NewMI = addRegReg(MIB, SrcReg, isKill, SrcReg2, isKill2);
1502 
1503  // Add kills if classifyLEAReg created a new register.
1504  if (LV) {
1505  if (SrcReg2 != Src2.getReg())
1506  LV->getVarInfo(SrcReg2).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1507  if (SrcReg != SrcReg2 && SrcReg != Src.getReg())
1508  LV->getVarInfo(SrcReg).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1509  }
1510  NumRegOperands = 3;
1511  break;
1512  }
1513  case X86::ADD8rr:
1514  case X86::ADD8rr_DB:
1515  Is8BitOp = true;
1516  [[fallthrough]];
1517  case X86::ADD16rr:
1518  case X86::ADD16rr_DB:
1519  return convertToThreeAddressWithLEA(MIOpc, MI, LV, LIS, Is8BitOp);
1520  case X86::ADD64ri32:
1521  case X86::ADD64ri8:
1522  case X86::ADD64ri32_DB:
1523  case X86::ADD64ri8_DB:
1524  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown add instruction!");
1525  NewMI = addOffset(
1526  BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(X86::LEA64r)).add(Dest).add(Src),
1527  MI.getOperand(2));
1528  break;
1529  case X86::ADD32ri:
1530  case X86::ADD32ri8:
1531  case X86::ADD32ri_DB:
1532  case X86::ADD32ri8_DB: {
1533  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown add instruction!");
1534  unsigned Opc = Is64Bit ? X86::LEA64_32r : X86::LEA32r;
1535 
1536  bool isKill;
1537  MachineOperand ImplicitOp = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0, false);
1538  if (!classifyLEAReg(MI, Src, Opc, /*AllowSP=*/true, SrcReg, isKill,
1539  ImplicitOp, LV, LIS))
1540  return nullptr;
1541 
1542  MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc))
1543  .add(Dest)
1544  .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(isKill));
1545  if (ImplicitOp.getReg() != 0)
1546  MIB.add(ImplicitOp);
1547 
1548  NewMI = addOffset(MIB, MI.getOperand(2));
1549 
1550  // Add kills if classifyLEAReg created a new register.
1551  if (LV && SrcReg != Src.getReg())
1552  LV->getVarInfo(SrcReg).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1553  break;
1554  }
1555  case X86::ADD8ri:
1556  case X86::ADD8ri_DB:
1557  Is8BitOp = true;
1558  [[fallthrough]];
1559  case X86::ADD16ri:
1560  case X86::ADD16ri8:
1561  case X86::ADD16ri_DB:
1562  case X86::ADD16ri8_DB:
1563  return convertToThreeAddressWithLEA(MIOpc, MI, LV, LIS, Is8BitOp);
1564  case X86::SUB8ri:
1565  case X86::SUB16ri8:
1566  case X86::SUB16ri:
1567  /// FIXME: Support these similar to ADD8ri/ADD16ri*.
1568  return nullptr;
1569  case X86::SUB32ri8:
1570  case X86::SUB32ri: {
1571  if (!MI.getOperand(2).isImm())
1572  return nullptr;
1573  int64_t Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
1574  if (!isInt<32>(-Imm))
1575  return nullptr;
1576 
1577  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown add instruction!");
1578  unsigned Opc = Is64Bit ? X86::LEA64_32r : X86::LEA32r;
1579 
1580  bool isKill;
1581  MachineOperand ImplicitOp = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0, false);
1582  if (!classifyLEAReg(MI, Src, Opc, /*AllowSP=*/true, SrcReg, isKill,
1583  ImplicitOp, LV, LIS))
1584  return nullptr;
1585 
1586  MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc))
1587  .add(Dest)
1588  .addReg(SrcReg, getKillRegState(isKill));
1589  if (ImplicitOp.getReg() != 0)
1590  MIB.add(ImplicitOp);
1591 
1592  NewMI = addOffset(MIB, -Imm);
1593 
1594  // Add kills if classifyLEAReg created a new register.
1595  if (LV && SrcReg != Src.getReg())
1596  LV->getVarInfo(SrcReg).Kills.push_back(NewMI);
1597  break;
1598  }
1599 
1600  case X86::SUB64ri8:
1601  case X86::SUB64ri32: {
1602  if (!MI.getOperand(2).isImm())
1603  return nullptr;
1604  int64_t Imm = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
1605  if (!isInt<32>(-Imm))
1606  return nullptr;
1607 
1608  assert(MI.getNumOperands() >= 3 && "Unknown sub instruction!");
1609 
1610  MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(),
1611  get(X86::LEA64r)).add(Dest).add(Src);
1612  NewMI = addOffset(MIB, -Imm);
1613  break;
1614  }
1615 
1616  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z128rmk:
1617  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z256rmk:
1618  case X86::VMOVDQU8Zrmk:
1619  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z128rmk:
1620  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z256rmk:
1621  case X86::VMOVDQU16Zrmk:
1622  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z128rmk: case X86::VMOVDQA32Z128rmk:
1623  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z256rmk: case X86::VMOVDQA32Z256rmk:
1624  case X86::VMOVDQU32Zrmk: case X86::VMOVDQA32Zrmk:
1625  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z128rmk: case X86::VMOVDQA64Z128rmk:
1626  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z256rmk: case X86::VMOVDQA64Z256rmk:
1627  case X86::VMOVDQU64Zrmk: case X86::VMOVDQA64Zrmk:
1628  case X86::VMOVUPDZ128rmk: case X86::VMOVAPDZ128rmk:
1629  case X86::VMOVUPDZ256rmk: case X86::VMOVAPDZ256rmk:
1630  case X86::VMOVUPDZrmk: case X86::VMOVAPDZrmk:
1631  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rmk: case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rmk:
1632  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rmk: case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rmk:
1633  case X86::VMOVUPSZrmk: case X86::VMOVAPSZrmk:
1634  case X86::VBROADCASTSDZ256rmk:
1635  case X86::VBROADCASTSDZrmk:
1636  case X86::VBROADCASTSSZ128rmk:
1637  case X86::VBROADCASTSSZ256rmk:
1638  case X86::VBROADCASTSSZrmk:
1639  case X86::VPBROADCASTDZ128rmk:
1640  case X86::VPBROADCASTDZ256rmk:
1641  case X86::VPBROADCASTDZrmk:
1642  case X86::VPBROADCASTQZ128rmk:
1643  case X86::VPBROADCASTQZ256rmk:
1644  case X86::VPBROADCASTQZrmk: {
1645  unsigned Opc;
1646  switch (MIOpc) {
1647  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
1648  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMBZ128rmk; break;
1649  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMBZ256rmk; break;
1650  case X86::VMOVDQU8Zrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMBZrmk; break;
1651  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMWZ128rmk; break;
1652  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMWZ256rmk; break;
1653  case X86::VMOVDQU16Zrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMWZrmk; break;
1654  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ128rmk; break;
1655  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ256rmk; break;
1656  case X86::VMOVDQU32Zrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZrmk; break;
1657  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ128rmk; break;
1658  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ256rmk; break;
1659  case X86::VMOVDQU64Zrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZrmk; break;
1660  case X86::VMOVUPDZ128rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ128rmk; break;
1661  case X86::VMOVUPDZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ256rmk; break;
1662  case X86::VMOVUPDZrmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZrmk; break;
1663  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ128rmk; break;
1664  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ256rmk; break;
1665  case X86::VMOVUPSZrmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZrmk; break;
1666  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ128rmk; break;
1667  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ256rmk; break;
1668  case X86::VMOVDQA32Zrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZrmk; break;
1669  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ128rmk; break;
1670  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ256rmk; break;
1671  case X86::VMOVDQA64Zrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZrmk; break;
1672  case X86::VMOVAPDZ128rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ128rmk; break;
1673  case X86::VMOVAPDZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ256rmk; break;
1674  case X86::VMOVAPDZrmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZrmk; break;
1675  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ128rmk; break;
1676  case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ256rmk; break;
1677  case X86::VMOVAPSZrmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZrmk; break;
1678  case X86::VBROADCASTSDZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ256rmbk; break;
1679  case X86::VBROADCASTSDZrmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZrmbk; break;
1680  case X86::VBROADCASTSSZ128rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ128rmbk; break;
1681  case X86::VBROADCASTSSZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ256rmbk; break;
1682  case X86::VBROADCASTSSZrmk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZrmbk; break;
1683  case X86::VPBROADCASTDZ128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ128rmbk; break;
1684  case X86::VPBROADCASTDZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ256rmbk; break;
1685  case X86::VPBROADCASTDZrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZrmbk; break;
1686  case X86::VPBROADCASTQZ128rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ128rmbk; break;
1687  case X86::VPBROADCASTQZ256rmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ256rmbk; break;
1688  case X86::VPBROADCASTQZrmk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZrmbk; break;
1689  }
1690 
1691  NewMI = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc))
1692  .add(Dest)
1693  .add(MI.getOperand(2))
1694  .add(Src)
1695  .add(MI.getOperand(3))
1696  .add(MI.getOperand(4))
1697  .add(MI.getOperand(5))
1698  .add(MI.getOperand(6))
1699  .add(MI.getOperand(7));
1700  NumRegOperands = 4;
1701  break;
1702  }
1703 
1704  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z128rrk:
1705  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z256rrk:
1706  case X86::VMOVDQU8Zrrk:
1707  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z128rrk:
1708  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z256rrk:
1709  case X86::VMOVDQU16Zrrk:
1710  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z128rrk: case X86::VMOVDQA32Z128rrk:
1711  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z256rrk: case X86::VMOVDQA32Z256rrk:
1712  case X86::VMOVDQU32Zrrk: case X86::VMOVDQA32Zrrk:
1713  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z128rrk: case X86::VMOVDQA64Z128rrk:
1714  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z256rrk: case X86::VMOVDQA64Z256rrk:
1715  case X86::VMOVDQU64Zrrk: case X86::VMOVDQA64Zrrk:
1716  case X86::VMOVUPDZ128rrk: case X86::VMOVAPDZ128rrk:
1717  case X86::VMOVUPDZ256rrk: case X86::VMOVAPDZ256rrk:
1718  case X86::VMOVUPDZrrk: case X86::VMOVAPDZrrk:
1719  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rrk: case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rrk:
1720  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rrk: case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rrk:
1721  case X86::VMOVUPSZrrk: case X86::VMOVAPSZrrk: {
1722  unsigned Opc;
1723  switch (MIOpc) {
1724  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
1725  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z128rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMBZ128rrk; break;
1726  case X86::VMOVDQU8Z256rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMBZ256rrk; break;
1727  case X86::VMOVDQU8Zrrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMBZrrk; break;
1728  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z128rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMWZ128rrk; break;
1729  case X86::VMOVDQU16Z256rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMWZ256rrk; break;
1730  case X86::VMOVDQU16Zrrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMWZrrk; break;
1731  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z128rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ128rrk; break;
1732  case X86::VMOVDQU32Z256rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ256rrk; break;
1733  case X86::VMOVDQU32Zrrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZrrk; break;
1734  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z128rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ128rrk; break;
1735  case X86::VMOVDQU64Z256rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ256rrk; break;
1736  case X86::VMOVDQU64Zrrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZrrk; break;
1737  case X86::VMOVUPDZ128rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ128rrk; break;
1738  case X86::VMOVUPDZ256rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ256rrk; break;
1739  case X86::VMOVUPDZrrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZrrk; break;
1740  case X86::VMOVUPSZ128rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ128rrk; break;
1741  case X86::VMOVUPSZ256rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ256rrk; break;
1742  case X86::VMOVUPSZrrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZrrk; break;
1743  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z128rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ128rrk; break;
1744  case X86::VMOVDQA32Z256rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZ256rrk; break;
1745  case X86::VMOVDQA32Zrrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMDZrrk; break;
1746  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z128rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ128rrk; break;
1747  case X86::VMOVDQA64Z256rrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZ256rrk; break;
1748  case X86::VMOVDQA64Zrrk: Opc = X86::VPBLENDMQZrrk; break;
1749  case X86::VMOVAPDZ128rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ128rrk; break;
1750  case X86::VMOVAPDZ256rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZ256rrk; break;
1751  case X86::VMOVAPDZrrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPDZrrk; break;
1752  case X86::VMOVAPSZ128rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ128rrk; break;
1753  case X86::VMOVAPSZ256rrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZ256rrk; break;
1754  case X86::VMOVAPSZrrk: Opc = X86::VBLENDMPSZrrk; break;
1755  }
1756 
1757  NewMI = BuildMI(MF, MI.getDebugLoc(), get(Opc))
1758  .add(Dest)
1759  .add(MI.getOperand(2))
1760  .add(Src)
1761  .add(MI.getOperand(3));
1762  NumRegOperands = 4;
1763  break;
1764  }
1765  }
1766 
1767  if (!NewMI) return nullptr;
1768 
1769  if (LV) { // Update live variables
1770  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumRegOperands; ++I) {
1771  MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(I);
1772  if (Op.isReg() && (Op.isDead() || Op.isKill()))
1773  LV->replaceKillInstruction(Op.getReg(), MI, *NewMI);
1774  }
1775  }
1776 
1777  MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent();
1778  MBB.insert(MI.getIterator(), NewMI); // Insert the new inst
1779 
1780  if (LIS) {
1781  LIS->ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(MI, *NewMI);
1782  if (SrcReg)
1783  LIS->getInterval(SrcReg);
1784  if (SrcReg2)
1785  LIS->getInterval(SrcReg2);
1786  }
1787 
1788  return NewMI;
1789 }
1790 
1791 /// This determines which of three possible cases of a three source commute
1792 /// the source indexes correspond to taking into account any mask operands.
1793 /// All prevents commuting a passthru operand. Returns -1 if the commute isn't
1794 /// possible.
1795 /// Case 0 - Possible to commute the first and second operands.
1796 /// Case 1 - Possible to commute the first and third operands.
1797 /// Case 2 - Possible to commute the second and third operands.
1798 static unsigned getThreeSrcCommuteCase(uint64_t TSFlags, unsigned SrcOpIdx1,
1799  unsigned SrcOpIdx2) {
1800  // Put the lowest index to SrcOpIdx1 to simplify the checks below.
1801  if (SrcOpIdx1 > SrcOpIdx2)
1802  std::swap(SrcOpIdx1, SrcOpIdx2);
1803 
1804  unsigned Op1 = 1, Op2 = 2, Op3 = 3;
1805  if (X86II::isKMasked(TSFlags)) {
1806  Op2++;
1807  Op3++;
1808  }
1809 
1810  if (SrcOpIdx1 == Op1 && SrcOpIdx2 == Op2)
1811  return 0;
1812  if (SrcOpIdx1 == Op1 && SrcOpIdx2 == Op3)
1813  return 1;
1814  if (SrcOpIdx1 == Op2 && SrcOpIdx2 == Op3)
1815  return 2;
1816  llvm_unreachable("Unknown three src commute case.");
1817 }
1818 
1819 unsigned X86InstrInfo::getFMA3OpcodeToCommuteOperands(
1820  const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned SrcOpIdx1, unsigned SrcOpIdx2,
1821  const X86InstrFMA3Group &FMA3Group) const {
1822 
1823  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
1824 
1825  // TODO: Commuting the 1st operand of FMA*_Int requires some additional
1826  // analysis. The commute optimization is legal only if all users of FMA*_Int
1827  // use only the lowest element of the FMA*_Int instruction. Such analysis are
1828  // not implemented yet. So, just return 0 in that case.
1829  // When such analysis are available this place will be the right place for
1830  // calling it.
1831  assert(!(FMA3Group.isIntrinsic() && (SrcOpIdx1 == 1 || SrcOpIdx2 == 1)) &&
1832  "Intrinsic instructions can't commute operand 1");
1833 
1834  // Determine which case this commute is or if it can't be done.
1835  unsigned Case = getThreeSrcCommuteCase(MI.getDesc().TSFlags, SrcOpIdx1,
1836  SrcOpIdx2);
1837  assert(Case < 3 && "Unexpected case number!");
1838 
1839  // Define the FMA forms mapping array that helps to map input FMA form
1840  // to output FMA form to preserve the operation semantics after
1841  // commuting the operands.
1842  const unsigned Form132Index = 0;
1843  const unsigned Form213Index = 1;
1844  const unsigned Form231Index = 2;
1845  static const unsigned FormMapping[][3] = {
1846  // 0: SrcOpIdx1 == 1 && SrcOpIdx2 == 2;
1847  // FMA132 A, C, b; ==> FMA231 C, A, b;
1848  // FMA213 B, A, c; ==> FMA213 A, B, c;
1849  // FMA231 C, A, b; ==> FMA132 A, C, b;
1850  { Form231Index, Form213Index, Form132Index },
1851  // 1: SrcOpIdx1 == 1 && SrcOpIdx2 == 3;
1852  // FMA132 A, c, B; ==> FMA132 B, c, A;
1853  // FMA213 B, a, C; ==> FMA231 C, a, B;
1854  // FMA231 C, a, B; ==> FMA213 B, a, C;
1855  { Form132Index, Form231Index, Form213Index },
1856  // 2: SrcOpIdx1 == 2 && SrcOpIdx2 == 3;
1857  // FMA132 a, C, B; ==> FMA213 a, B, C;
1858  // FMA213 b, A, C; ==> FMA132 b, C, A;
1859  // FMA231 c, A, B; ==> FMA231 c, B, A;
1860  { Form213Index, Form132Index, Form231Index }
1861  };
1862 
1863  unsigned FMAForms[3];
1864  FMAForms[0] = FMA3Group.get132Opcode();
1865  FMAForms[1] = FMA3Group.get213Opcode();
1866  FMAForms[2] = FMA3Group.get231Opcode();
1867 
1868  // Everything is ready, just adjust the FMA opcode and return it.
1869  for (unsigned FormIndex = 0; FormIndex < 3; FormIndex++)
1870  if (Opc == FMAForms[FormIndex])
1871  return FMAForms[FormMapping[Case][FormIndex]];
1872 
1873  llvm_unreachable("Illegal FMA3 format");
1874 }
1875 
1876 static void commuteVPTERNLOG(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned SrcOpIdx1,
1877  unsigned SrcOpIdx2) {
1878  // Determine which case this commute is or if it can't be done.
1879  unsigned Case = getThreeSrcCommuteCase(MI.getDesc().TSFlags, SrcOpIdx1,
1880  SrcOpIdx2);
1881  assert(Case < 3 && "Unexpected case value!");
1882 
1883  // For each case we need to swap two pairs of bits in the final immediate.
1884  static const uint8_t SwapMasks[3][4] = {
1885  { 0x04, 0x10, 0x08, 0x20 }, // Swap bits 2/4 and 3/5.
1886  { 0x02, 0x10, 0x08, 0x40 }, // Swap bits 1/4 and 3/6.
1887  { 0x02, 0x04, 0x20, 0x40 }, // Swap bits 1/2 and 5/6.
1888  };
1889 
1890  uint8_t Imm = MI.getOperand(MI.getNumOperands()-1).getImm();
1891  // Clear out the bits we are swapping.
1892  uint8_t NewImm = Imm & ~(SwapMasks[Case][0] | SwapMasks[Case][1] |
1893  SwapMasks[Case][2] | SwapMasks[Case][3]);
1894  // If the immediate had a bit of the pair set, then set the opposite bit.
1895  if (Imm & SwapMasks[Case][0]) NewImm |= SwapMasks[Case][1];
1896  if (Imm & SwapMasks[Case][1]) NewImm |= SwapMasks[Case][0];
1897  if (Imm & SwapMasks[Case][2]) NewImm |= SwapMasks[Case][3];
1898  if (Imm & SwapMasks[Case][3]) NewImm |= SwapMasks[Case][2];
1899  MI.getOperand(MI.getNumOperands()-1).setImm(NewImm);
1900 }
1901 
1902 // Returns true if this is a VPERMI2 or VPERMT2 instruction that can be
1903 // commuted.
1904 static bool isCommutableVPERMV3Instruction(unsigned Opcode) {
1905 #define VPERM_CASES(Suffix) \
1906  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##128rr: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##128rr: \
1907  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##256rr: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##256rr: \
1908  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##rr: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##rr: \
1909  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##128rm: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##128rm: \
1910  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##256rm: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##256rm: \
1911  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##rm: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##rm: \
1912  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##128rrkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##128rrkz: \
1913  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##256rrkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##256rrkz: \
1914  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##rrkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##rrkz: \
1915  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##128rmkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##128rmkz: \
1916  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##256rmkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##256rmkz: \
1917  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##rmkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##rmkz:
1918 
1919 #define VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(Suffix) \
1920  VPERM_CASES(Suffix) \
1921  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##128rmb: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##128rmb: \
1922  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##256rmb: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##256rmb: \
1923  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##rmb: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##rmb: \
1924  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##128rmbkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##128rmbkz: \
1925  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##256rmbkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##256rmbkz: \
1926  case X86::VPERMI2##Suffix##rmbkz: case X86::VPERMT2##Suffix##rmbkz:
1927 
1928  switch (Opcode) {
1929  default: return false;
1930  VPERM_CASES(B)
1931  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(D)
1932  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(PD)
1933  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(PS)
1934  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(Q)
1935  VPERM_CASES(W)
1936  return true;
1937  }
1938 #undef VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST
1939 #undef VPERM_CASES
1940 }
1941 
1942 // Returns commuted opcode for VPERMI2 and VPERMT2 instructions by switching
1943 // from the I opcode to the T opcode and vice versa.
1944 static unsigned getCommutedVPERMV3Opcode(unsigned Opcode) {
1945 #define VPERM_CASES(Orig, New) \
1946  case X86::Orig##128rr: return X86::New##128rr; \
1947  case X86::Orig##128rrkz: return X86::New##128rrkz; \
1948  case X86::Orig##128rm: return X86::New##128rm; \
1949  case X86::Orig##128rmkz: return X86::New##128rmkz; \
1950  case X86::Orig##256rr: return X86::New##256rr; \
1951  case X86::Orig##256rrkz: return X86::New##256rrkz; \
1952  case X86::Orig##256rm: return X86::New##256rm; \
1953  case X86::Orig##256rmkz: return X86::New##256rmkz; \
1954  case X86::Orig##rr: return X86::New##rr; \
1955  case X86::Orig##rrkz: return X86::New##rrkz; \
1956  case X86::Orig##rm: return X86::New##rm; \
1957  case X86::Orig##rmkz: return X86::New##rmkz;
1958 
1959 #define VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(Orig, New) \
1960  VPERM_CASES(Orig, New) \
1961  case X86::Orig##128rmb: return X86::New##128rmb; \
1962  case X86::Orig##128rmbkz: return X86::New##128rmbkz; \
1963  case X86::Orig##256rmb: return X86::New##256rmb; \
1964  case X86::Orig##256rmbkz: return X86::New##256rmbkz; \
1965  case X86::Orig##rmb: return X86::New##rmb; \
1966  case X86::Orig##rmbkz: return X86::New##rmbkz;
1967 
1968  switch (Opcode) {
1969  VPERM_CASES(VPERMI2B, VPERMT2B)
1970  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMI2D, VPERMT2D)
1971  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMI2PD, VPERMT2PD)
1972  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMI2PS, VPERMT2PS)
1973  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMI2Q, VPERMT2Q)
1974  VPERM_CASES(VPERMI2W, VPERMT2W)
1975  VPERM_CASES(VPERMT2B, VPERMI2B)
1976  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMT2D, VPERMI2D)
1977  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMT2PD, VPERMI2PD)
1978  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMT2PS, VPERMI2PS)
1979  VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST(VPERMT2Q, VPERMI2Q)
1980  VPERM_CASES(VPERMT2W, VPERMI2W)
1981  }
1982 
1983  llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
1984 #undef VPERM_CASES_BROADCAST
1985 #undef VPERM_CASES
1986 }
1987 
1988 MachineInstr *X86InstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(MachineInstr &MI, bool NewMI,
1989  unsigned OpIdx1,
1990  unsigned OpIdx2) const {
1991  auto cloneIfNew = [NewMI](MachineInstr &MI) -> MachineInstr & {
1992  if (NewMI)
1993  return *MI.getParent()->getParent()->CloneMachineInstr(&MI);
1994  return MI;
1995  };
1996 
1997  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
1998  case X86::SHRD16rri8: // A = SHRD16rri8 B, C, I -> A = SHLD16rri8 C, B, (16-I)
1999  case X86::SHLD16rri8: // A = SHLD16rri8 B, C, I -> A = SHRD16rri8 C, B, (16-I)
2000  case X86::SHRD32rri8: // A = SHRD32rri8 B, C, I -> A = SHLD32rri8 C, B, (32-I)
2001  case X86::SHLD32rri8: // A = SHLD32rri8 B, C, I -> A = SHRD32rri8 C, B, (32-I)
2002  case X86::SHRD64rri8: // A = SHRD64rri8 B, C, I -> A = SHLD64rri8 C, B, (64-I)
2003  case X86::SHLD64rri8:{// A = SHLD64rri8 B, C, I -> A = SHRD64rri8 C, B, (64-I)
2004  unsigned Opc;
2005  unsigned Size;
2006  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2007  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
2008  case X86::SHRD16rri8: Size = 16; Opc = X86::SHLD16rri8; break;
2009  case X86::SHLD16rri8: Size = 16; Opc = X86::SHRD16rri8; break;
2010  case X86::SHRD32rri8: Size = 32; Opc = X86::SHLD32rri8; break;
2011  case X86::SHLD32rri8: Size = 32; Opc = X86::SHRD32rri8; break;
2012  case X86::SHRD64rri8: Size = 64; Opc = X86::SHLD64rri8; break;
2013  case X86::SHLD64rri8: Size = 64; Opc = X86::SHRD64rri8; break;
2014  }
2015  unsigned Amt = MI.getOperand(3).getImm();
2016  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2017  WorkingMI.setDesc(get(Opc));
2018  WorkingMI.getOperand(3).setImm(Size - Amt);
2019  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2020  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2021  }
2022  case X86::PFSUBrr:
2023  case X86::PFSUBRrr: {
2024  // PFSUB x, y: x = x - y
2025  // PFSUBR x, y: x = y - x
2026  unsigned Opc =
2027  (X86::PFSUBRrr == MI.getOpcode() ? X86::PFSUBrr : X86::PFSUBRrr);
2028  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2029  WorkingMI.setDesc(get(Opc));
2030  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2031  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2032  }
2033  case X86::BLENDPDrri:
2034  case X86::BLENDPSrri:
2035  case X86::VBLENDPDrri:
2036  case X86::VBLENDPSrri:
2037  // If we're optimizing for size, try to use MOVSD/MOVSS.
2038  if (MI.getParent()->getParent()->getFunction().hasOptSize()) {
2039  unsigned Mask, Opc;
2040  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2041  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
2042  case X86::BLENDPDrri: Opc = X86::MOVSDrr; Mask = 0x03; break;
2043  case X86::BLENDPSrri: Opc = X86::MOVSSrr; Mask = 0x0F; break;
2044  case X86::VBLENDPDrri: Opc = X86::VMOVSDrr; Mask = 0x03; break;
2045  case X86::VBLENDPSrri: Opc = X86::VMOVSSrr; Mask = 0x0F; break;
2046  }
2047  if ((MI.getOperand(3).getImm() ^ Mask) == 1) {
2048  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2049  WorkingMI.setDesc(get(Opc));
2050  WorkingMI.removeOperand(3);
2051  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI,
2052  /*NewMI=*/false,
2053  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2054  }
2055  }
2056  [[fallthrough]];
2057  case X86::PBLENDWrri:
2058  case X86::VBLENDPDYrri:
2059  case X86::VBLENDPSYrri:
2060  case X86::VPBLENDDrri:
2061  case X86::VPBLENDWrri:
2062  case X86::VPBLENDDYrri:
2063  case X86::VPBLENDWYrri:{
2064  int8_t Mask;
2065  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2066  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
2067  case X86::BLENDPDrri: Mask = (int8_t)0x03; break;
2068  case X86::BLENDPSrri: Mask = (int8_t)0x0F; break;
2069  case X86::PBLENDWrri: Mask = (int8_t)0xFF; break;
2070  case X86::VBLENDPDrri: Mask = (int8_t)0x03; break;
2071  case X86::VBLENDPSrri: Mask = (int8_t)0x0F; break;
2072  case X86::VBLENDPDYrri: Mask = (int8_t)0x0F; break;
2073  case X86::VBLENDPSYrri: Mask = (int8_t)0xFF; break;
2074  case X86::VPBLENDDrri: Mask = (int8_t)0x0F; break;
2075  case X86::VPBLENDWrri: Mask = (int8_t)0xFF; break;
2076  case X86::VPBLENDDYrri: Mask = (int8_t)0xFF; break;
2077  case X86::VPBLENDWYrri: Mask = (int8_t)0xFF; break;
2078  }
2079  // Only the least significant bits of Imm are used.
2080  // Using int8_t to ensure it will be sign extended to the int64_t that
2081  // setImm takes in order to match isel behavior.
2082  int8_t Imm = MI.getOperand(3).getImm() & Mask;
2083  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2084  WorkingMI.getOperand(3).setImm(Mask ^ Imm);
2085  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2086  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2087  }
2088  case X86::INSERTPSrr:
2089  case X86::VINSERTPSrr:
2090  case X86::VINSERTPSZrr: {
2091  unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(MI.getNumOperands() - 1).getImm();
2092  unsigned ZMask = Imm & 15;
2093  unsigned DstIdx = (Imm >> 4) & 3;
2094  unsigned SrcIdx = (Imm >> 6) & 3;
2095 
2096  // We can commute insertps if we zero 2 of the elements, the insertion is
2097  // "inline" and we don't override the insertion with a zero.
2098  if (DstIdx == SrcIdx && (ZMask & (1 << DstIdx)) == 0 &&
2099  llvm::popcount(ZMask) == 2) {
2100  unsigned AltIdx = llvm::countr_zero((ZMask | (1 << DstIdx)) ^ 15);
2101  assert(AltIdx < 4 && "Illegal insertion index");
2102  unsigned AltImm = (AltIdx << 6) | (AltIdx << 4) | ZMask;
2103  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2104  WorkingMI.getOperand(MI.getNumOperands() - 1).setImm(AltImm);
2105  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2106  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2107  }
2108  return nullptr;
2109  }
2110  case X86::MOVSDrr:
2111  case X86::MOVSSrr:
2112  case X86::VMOVSDrr:
2113  case X86::VMOVSSrr:{
2114  // On SSE41 or later we can commute a MOVSS/MOVSD to a BLENDPS/BLENDPD.
2115  if (Subtarget.hasSSE41()) {
2116  unsigned Mask, Opc;
2117  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
2118  default: llvm_unreachable("Unreachable!");
2119  case X86::MOVSDrr: Opc = X86::BLENDPDrri; Mask = 0x02; break;
2120  case X86::MOVSSrr: Opc = X86::BLENDPSrri; Mask = 0x0E; break;
2121  case X86::VMOVSDrr: Opc = X86::VBLENDPDrri; Mask = 0x02; break;
2122  case X86::VMOVSSrr: Opc = X86::VBLENDPSrri; Mask = 0x0E; break;
2123  }
2124 
2125  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2126  WorkingMI.setDesc(get(Opc));
2127  WorkingMI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(Mask));
2128  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2129  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2130  }
2131 
2132  // Convert to SHUFPD.
2133  assert(MI.getOpcode() == X86::MOVSDrr &&
2134  "Can only commute MOVSDrr without SSE4.1");
2135 
2136  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2137  WorkingMI.setDesc(get(X86::SHUFPDrri));
2138  WorkingMI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(0x02));
2139  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2140  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2141  }
2142  case X86::SHUFPDrri: {
2143  // Commute to MOVSD.
2144  assert(MI.getOperand(3).getImm() == 0x02 && "Unexpected immediate!");
2145  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2146  WorkingMI.setDesc(get(X86::MOVSDrr));
2147  WorkingMI.removeOperand(3);
2148  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2149  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2150  }
2151  case X86::PCLMULQDQrr:
2152  case X86::VPCLMULQDQrr:
2153  case X86::VPCLMULQDQYrr:
2154  case X86::VPCLMULQDQZrr:
2155  case X86::VPCLMULQDQZ128rr:
2156  case X86::VPCLMULQDQZ256rr: {
2157  // SRC1 64bits = Imm[0] ? SRC1[127:64] : SRC1[63:0]
2158  // SRC2 64bits = Imm[4] ? SRC2[127:64] : SRC2[63:0]
2159  unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(3).getImm();
2160  unsigned Src1Hi = Imm & 0x01;
2161  unsigned Src2Hi = Imm & 0x10;
2162  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2163  WorkingMI.getOperand(3).setImm((Src1Hi << 4) | (Src2Hi >> 4));
2164  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2165  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2166  }
2167  case X86::VPCMPBZ128rri: case X86::VPCMPUBZ128rri:
2168  case X86::VPCMPBZ256rri: case X86::VPCMPUBZ256rri:
2169  case X86::VPCMPBZrri: case X86::VPCMPUBZrri:
2170  case X86::VPCMPDZ128rri: case X86::VPCMPUDZ128rri:
2171  case X86::VPCMPDZ256rri: case X86::VPCMPUDZ256rri:

2173  case X86::VPCMPQZ128rri: case X86::VPCMPUQZ128rri:
2174  case X86::VPCMPQZ256rri: case X86::VPCMPUQZ256rri:
2175  case X86::VPCMPQZrri: case X86::VPCMPUQZrri:
2176  case X86::VPCMPWZ128rri: case X86::VPCMPUWZ128rri:
2177  case X86::VPCMPWZ256rri: case X86::VPCMPUWZ256rri:
2178  case X86::VPCMPWZrri: case X86::VPCMPUWZrri:
2179  case X86::VPCMPBZ128rrik: case X86::VPCMPUBZ128rrik:
2180  case X86::VPCMPBZ256rrik: case X86::VPCMPUBZ256rrik:
2181  case X86::VPCMPBZrrik: case X86::VPCMPUBZrrik:
2182  case X86::VPCMPDZ128rrik: case X86::VPCMPUDZ128rrik:
2183  case X86::VPCMPDZ256rrik: case X86::VPCMPUDZ256rrik:
2184  case X86::VPCMPDZrrik: case X86::VPCMPUDZrrik:

2186  case X86::VPCMPQZ256rrik: case X86::VPCMPUQZ256rrik:
2187  case X86::VPCMPQZrrik: case X86::VPCMPUQZrrik:
2188  case X86::VPCMPWZ128rrik: case X86::VPCMPUWZ128rrik:
2189  case X86::VPCMPWZ256rrik: case X86::VPCMPUWZ256rrik:
2190  case X86::VPCMPWZrrik: case X86::VPCMPUWZrrik: {

2192  unsigned Imm = MI.getOperand(MI.getNumOperands() - 1).getImm() & 0x7;
2193  Imm = X86::getSwappedVPCMPImm(Imm);
2194  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);

2197  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2198  }
2199  case X86::VPCOMBri: case X86::VPCOMUBri:
2200  case X86::VPCOMDri: case X86::VPCOMUDri:
2201  case X86::VPCOMQri: case X86::VPCOMUQri:
2202  case X86::VPCOMWri: case X86::VPCOMUWri: {
2203  // Flip comparison mode immediate (if necessary).

2205  Imm = X86::getSwappedVPCOMImm(Imm);
2206  auto &WorkingMI = cloneIfNew(MI);
2207  WorkingMI.getOperand(3).setImm(Imm);
2208  return TargetInstrInfo::commuteInstructionImpl(WorkingMI, /*NewMI=*/false,
2209  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2210  }
2211  case X86::VCMPSDZrr:
2212  case X86::VCMPSSZrr:
2213  case X86::VCMPPDZrri:
2214  case X86::VCMPPSZrri:
2215  case X86::VCMPSHZrr:
2216  case X86::VCMPPHZrri:
2217  case X86::VCMPPHZ128rri:
2218  case X86::VCMPPHZ256rri:
2219  case X86::VCMPPDZ128rri:
2220  case X86::VCMPPSZ128rri:
2221  case X86::VCMPPDZ256rri:
2222  case X86::VCMPPSZ256rri:
2223  case X86::VCMPPDZrrik:

2235  OpIdx1, OpIdx2);
2236  }
2237  case X86::VPERM2F128rr:
2238  case X86::VPERM2I128rr: {
2239  // Flip permute source immediate.
2240  // Imm & 0x02: lo = if set, select Op1.lo/hi else Op0.lo/hi.
2241  // Imm & 0x20: hi = if set, select Op1.lo/hi else Op0.lo/hi.
2242  int8_t Imm = MI.getOperand(3).getImm() & 0xFF;

2248  case X86::MOVHLPSrr:

2250  case X86::VMOVHLPSrr:
2251  case X86::VUNPCKHPDrr:
2252  case X86::VMOVHLPSZrr:
2253  case X86::VUNPCKHPDZ128rr: {
2254  assert(Subtarget.hasSSE2() && "Commuting MOVHLP/UNPCKHPD requires SSE2!");
2255
